# Project Euler 89: Roman Numerals
# Some of the 1000 Roman numerals in roman.txt aren't written in
# minimal form (e.g. "IIII" instead of "IV", or "DCCCC" instead of
# "CM"). Find the total number of characters saved by rewriting every
# one of them minimally.
# Answer: 743
# Note: BARE has no file I/O, so roman.txt is pasted in directly as a
# list of strings below, the same technique every file-dependent
# problem in this set uses. Each numeral is parsed to a number (the
# standard rule: a symbol worth less than the one right after it is
# subtracted rather than added, e.g. IV = 5-1), then rebuilt from
# scratch using the largest-symbol-first greedy method, which always
# produces the shortest valid form. The savings is just old length
# minus new length, summed over all 1000.

